## Key features

* High efficiency (10M docs indexed in 7 mins, 2.5ms search latency, 1.6K req/s throughput)
* Supports Chinese word segmentation (using [sego](https://github.com/huichen/sego))
* Supports computing token proximity
* Supports computing BM25 relevance
* Supports ranking with custom scoring criteria
* Supports adding and removing index online
* Extensibility to support distributed search
* Released under Apache License v2

Demo http://soooweibo.com

## Install/Update

First install dependencies

    go get -u github.com/huichen/sego
    go get -u github.com/huichen/murmur

Then install Wukong engine

    go get -u github.com/huichen/wukong

Need Go version >= 1.1.1

## Usage

The simplest example

```go
package main

import (
    "github.com/huichen/wukong/engine"
    "github.com/huichen/wukong/types"
    "log"
)

var (
    // searcher is goroutine safe
    searcher = engine.Engine{}
)

func main() {
    // Initialization
    searcher.Init(types.EngineInitOptions{
        SegmenterDictionaries: "github.com/huichen/wukong/data/dictionary.txt"})

    // Add documents to index
    searcher.IndexDocument(0, types.DocumentIndexData{
        Content: "Baidu's acquisition will be the most expensive one in the history of Chinaâ€™s web industry."})
    searcher.IndexDocument(1, types.DocumentIndexData{
        Content: "Baidu agrees to acquire mobile-app store operator 91 Wireless for $1.9 billion."})
    searcher.IndexDocument(2, types.DocumentIndexData{
        Content: "Baidu is the most popular search engine in China."})

    // Wait until all docs are indexed
    searcher.FlushIndex()

    // Search
    log.Print(searcher.Search(types.SearchRequest{Text:"Baidu China"}))
}
```

Isn't it simple!

Then check out a [codelab](https://github.com/huichen/wukong/blob/master/docs/en/codelab.md) that teaches you how to write a Weibo search website in less than 200 lines of Go code.
